column309: "text":"<p>The Pentagon told reporters Wednesday that 51 laboratories received shipments of anthrax
column310: across 17 states (plus D.C.) and three foreign countries over a period of <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/wjhenn/status/606175488416096256\">at least 10 years</a>. But the scare is not over—the Pentagon expects that number to rise.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/06/02/pentagon-doesn-t-know-where-anthrax-went.html\">Anthrax was even detected at the Pentagon</a> yesterday
column311: The Daily Beast’s Nancy Youssef reported
column312: when the Defense Department admitted it didn’t know everywhere it had sent the lethal bacteria. As many as 31 people are undergoing prophylactic antibiotic treatment for exposure
column313: although there is no evidence yet that anyone has gotten ill from the shipments.</p>\n<p>So far

column315: and all have come up positive. The Pentagon has not yet announced which labs received the potent samples.</p>\n"
